<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Find all functions \(f: \mathbb{Z}^2 \to [0, 1]\) such that for any integers \(x\) and \(y\), \[2f(x, y) = f(x - 1, y) + f(x, y - 1)\]</p>
